args: The hell's gotten into you, Noelle?\nWhy'd you drag me into Kirsty's office?
B-because if I don't t-tell you this now,\nI...I know I'll regret it!
After hearing about your sister, I couldn't\njust...watch you suffer like that.
That's when I remembered that Kirsty\ntold me something, um, important here\nin her office once.
About what it means to...to be\nresponsible for another's life.
I'll do my best to repeat it, so just listen.\nI'd done something...unforgivable and,\num, this is what she told me!
An order I had delivered led to a squadron taking\nmassive losses, and I was beside myself.
I'm sorry, Commander Kirsty. I'm so sorry!\nI messed up, and now everyone isâ€”
Enough, Noelle. You carried out your\nmission as a messenger, which is all\nthat anyone can ask.
B-but I'd noticed the orders were wrong,\nI should have...
A messenger's job is to relay the orders\nshe's given, word for word. It's we officers\nwho bear responsibility for the contents.
So any loss of life that resulted from this\noperation is on my hands, not yours.\nGot it?
That's not... How can it ALL be your\nresponsibility, Commander?!
I c-can't accept that... I'd be scared to\nDEATH if all that responsibility was on me!
You're kind to say so. And yes, I AM\nscared to think of how many lives are\nresting on my narrow shoulders.

Just thinking about it is...dizzying.
When lives hang on your every judgment,
you have to be either a fool or a
psychopath not to be scared.
But I still stand in this war room,\nbecause that is a commander's job.
If you're that scared, Commander,\nthen...why stay here?
By staying here, I win the chance at\nprotecting every life in my command.
No matter how frightening things may get,\nyou could never pry me away from that.
She's never said anything even remotely\nlike that around me.
That must be because she has, um,\nhigh expectations of you?
She wanted to be a model for you...\nEr, at least, that's what I think?
Then when she kept pressing me to accept\nthe promotion, that was...
She knew the fear I feltâ€”even shared it.\nAnd still she pushed me to...
She knows you, Joachim. Really well.
And she knows you're kind enough to not\nwant to lose anyone, and, um...strong\nenough to make it happen.
Yeah, she liked to make with the praise,\nall right. Every time I did something right,\nshe'd be the first one to tell me.
That's why I...yelled in front of everyone\nand...pulled you over here to ask...
I mean, I know holding another's life in\nyour hands is unbelievably, um, heavy,\na-and all the expectations...
But if we both feel the same, and we\ndon't want to see anyone else get hurt...
Please just do it, Joachim!\nWe NEED you!
No, don't apologize. Even I can't just keep\nstewing after hearing all that.
I feel like I finally understand what Kirsty's\nexpectations for me actually mean.
Running away's easy: just cover your eyes\nand pretend you never saw a thing. \nIt's what I've been doing this whole time.

Butâ€”and this sounds so obvious when
you say itâ€”but if I'd faced my troubles
head-on instead of running away, I might
have had the chance to save some lives.
I lost my sister, yeah. But right now I've\ngot more people I want to protect.\nNo more running.
Let's get back, Noelle. We don't have long\nuntil the enemy's ranks are reformed,\nand then things are gonna get real busy.
Welcome back. What were you two up\nto, anyway? Some kinda secret chitchat?
She had a message for me. From Kirsty.
Well, whatever it was, you look better.\nGuess that's not surprising after the boss\nlady put the fear of god in you.
So, what's the plan? Scouts are saying it\nlooks like the enemy's planning a night\nraid, which is bad news for us.
Yeah, they've got us beat hands-down in\nspellcasters. It'll be hard to handle them\nat night.
But that just means we have to hit 'em\nbefore that happens. And I've got a plan\nfor that, but it ain't pretty.
There's not a person here who doesn't trust\nyou with their life, remember?
Hey, I'm just stating the obvious.\nAnyway, fill us in already.
It's basically a repeat of earlier where we\nuse the manacaster as a diversion.\nExcept this time, we can't just sit back.
We keep their flanks pinned down and hit\ntheir command center, force a rout.\nWe charge as a groupâ€”all of us.
Ha! I love it! They think they've got\nthe numbers? Then we'll go straight\nfor the head.
I take full responsibility for this operation.
...Which is why I'm bringing every one of\nyou idiots home safe. Now move out!
